#: ../../source/intranet/windows/domain/attack.rst:2
msgid "攻击类型"
msgstr "Attack Types"

#: ../../source/intranet/windows/domain/attack.rst:5
msgid "黄金票据利用"
msgstr "Golden Ticket Exploitation"

#: ../../source/intranet/windows/domain/attack.rst:6
msgid "在认证过程中，经过client与AS的通信会得到TGT，黄金票据（Golden Ticket）就是伪造票据授予票据（TGT），也被称为认证票据。"
msgstr "During authentication, communication between the client and the AS obtains a TGT. A Golden Ticket is a forged ticket-granting ticket (TGT), also called an authentication ticket."

#: ../../source/intranet/windows/domain/attack.rst:8
msgid "黄金票据利用需要与DC通信，且需要获取krbtgt的hash，但是可以获取任何Kerbose服务权限。"
msgstr "Golden Ticket exploitation requires communication with the DC and the krbtgt hash, but it can obtain access to any Kerberos service."

#: ../../source/intranet/windows/domain/attack.rst:11
msgid "白银票据利用"
msgstr "Silver Ticket Exploitation"

#: ../../source/intranet/windows/domain/attack.rst:12
msgid ""
"白银票据（Silver "
"Tickets）伪造利用的是Kerberos认证中的第三个步骤，在第三步的时候，client会带着ticket向server的某个服务进行请求，如果验证通过就可以访问server上的指定服务了，这里的ticket是基于client"
" info、server session key、end time、server hash。这里client info已知，end "
"time可以构造，server session key是TGS生成的，所以只要server的NTLM "
"hash即可。银票伪造的是TGS，只能访问指定的服务。"
msgstr "Silver Ticket forgery abuses the third step of Kerberos authentication. In that step, the client sends a request with a ticket to a service on the server. If validation succeeds, the client can access the specified service on the server. This ticket is based on client info, the server session key, end time, and server hash. Here the client info is known, the end time can be constructed, and the server session key is generated by the TGS, so only the server's NTLM hash is needed. A Silver Ticket forges a TGS and can only access the specified service."

#: ../../source/intranet/windows/domain/attack.rst:15
msgid "DCSync 攻击"
msgstr "DCSync Attack"

#: ../../source/intranet/windows/domain/attack.rst:16
msgid ""
"域内有多台域控服务器时，为了同步域控服务器的修改，微软提供了基于远程目录协议 `DRSR <https://docs.microsoft.com"
"/en-us/openspecs/windows_protocols/ms-drsr/f977faaa-673e-4f66-b9bf-"
"48c640241d47>`_ 的同步机制。"
msgstr "When a domain has multiple domain controllers, Microsoft provides a synchronization mechanism based on the remote directory protocol `DRSR <https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/openspecs/windows_protocols/ms-drsr/f977faaa-673e-4f66-b9bf-48c640241d47>`_ to synchronize changes between domain controllers."

#: ../../source/intranet/windows/domain/attack.rst:18
msgid ""
"在多个域控服务器之间，每隔一段时间会有一次域数据的同步。由需要同步的域控服务器向其它服务器发送 GetNCChanges "
"请求，请求中包含需要同步的数据。数据量较多时，则重复这个过程。"
msgstr "Domain data is synchronized between multiple domain controllers at intervals. The domain controller that needs synchronization sends GetNCChanges requests to other servers, and the requests contain the data to synchronize. When there is a large amount of data, this process is repeated."

#: ../../source/intranet/windows/domain/attack.rst:20
msgid ""
"DCSync 就是使用这种机制进行域渗透的技术，由Benjamin DELPY gentilkiwi和Vincent LE "
"TOUX共同编写，在2015年添加到 mimikatz 的一个功能，可以导出域内所有用户的hash。"
msgstr "DCSync is a domain penetration technique that uses this mechanism. It was jointly written by Benjamin DELPY gentilkiwi and Vincent LE TOUX, added to mimikatz in 2015, and can export the hashes of all users in a domain."

#: ../../source/intranet/windows/domain/attack.rst:22
msgid "这种方式需要满足以下任一一种权限："
msgstr "This method requires any one of the following privileges:"

#: ../../source/intranet/windows/domain/attack.rst:24
msgid "Administrators 组内的用户"
msgstr "A user in the Administrators group"

#: ../../source/intranet/windows/domain/attack.rst:25
msgid "Domain Admins 组内的用户"
msgstr "A user in the Domain Admins group"

#: ../../source/intranet/windows/domain/attack.rst:26
msgid "Enterprise Admins 组内的用户"
msgstr "A user in the Enterprise Admins group"

#: ../../source/intranet/windows/domain/attack.rst:27
msgid "域控制器的计算机帐户"
msgstr "A domain controller computer account"

#: ../../source/intranet/windows/domain/attack.rst:29
msgid "或者拥有特定的几条 DACL:"
msgstr "Or specific DACL entries:"

#: ../../source/intranet/windows/domain/attack.rst:31
msgid "DS-Replication-Get-Changes"
msgstr "DS-Replication-Get-Changes"

#: ../../source/intranet/windows/domain/attack.rst:32
msgid "DS-Replication-Get-Changes-All"
msgstr "DS-Replication-Get-Changes-All"

#: ../../source/intranet/windows/domain/attack.rst:33
msgid "DS-Replication-Get-Changes-In-Filtered-Set"
msgstr "DS-Replication-Get-Changes-In-Filtered-Set"

#: ../../source/intranet/windows/domain/attack.rst:35
msgid "当没有管理员用户，但是拥有 WriteDACL 权限时，可以写入上述 DACL 来完成 DCSync 。"
msgstr "When no administrator user is available but WriteDACL permission is present, the DACL entries above can be written to perform DCSync."

#: ../../source/intranet/windows/domain/attack.rst:37
msgid "对于这种攻击，可以通过检测 GetNCChanges 发起者的方式，如果由非域控机器发起对应请求，则可以认为是 DCSync 攻击。"
msgstr "This attack can be detected by checking the initiator of GetNCChanges. If the corresponding request is initiated by a non-domain-controller machine, it can be treated as a DCSync attack."

#: ../../source/intranet/windows/domain/attack.rst:40
msgid "DCShadow 攻击"
msgstr "DCShadow Attack"

#: ../../source/intranet/windows/domain/attack.rst:41
msgid ""
"DCShadow是由来自法国的安全研究人员Benjamin Delpy和Vincent Le Toux在2018年的微软蓝帽（Blue "
"Hat）大会上提出。"
msgstr "DCShadow was introduced by French security researchers Benjamin Delpy and Vincent Le Toux at Microsoft's Blue Hat conference in 2018."

#: ../../source/intranet/windows/domain/attack.rst:43
msgid "DCShadow攻击指在Active Directory环境下创建一个恶意的域控制器，并用它来推送恶意对象。"
msgstr "A DCShadow attack creates a malicious domain controller in an Active Directory environment and uses it to push malicious objects."

#: ../../source/intranet/windows/domain/attack.rst:46
msgid "哈希传递攻击"
msgstr "Pass-the-Hash Attack"

#: ../../source/intranet/windows/domain/attack.rst:47
msgid "哈希传递攻击（Pass-the-Hash，PTH）是通过传递NTLM哈希来认证的攻击方法，常用的工具有mimikatz等。"
msgstr "Pass-the-Hash (PTH) is an attack method that authenticates by passing NTLM hashes. Common tools include mimikatz."

#: ../../source/intranet/windows/domain/attack.rst:50
msgid "票据传递攻击"
msgstr "Pass-the-Ticket Attack"

#: ../../source/intranet/windows/domain/attack.rst:51
msgid ""
"票据传递攻击（Pass-the-Ticket "
"Attacks，PtT）是一种使用Kerberos票据代替明文密码或NTLM哈希的方法。PtT最常见的用途可能是使用黄金票据和白银票据，通过PtT访问主机相当简单。"
msgstr "Pass-the-Ticket (PtT) attacks use Kerberos tickets instead of plaintext passwords or NTLM hashes. The most common PtT use may be Golden Tickets and Silver Tickets, and accessing hosts through PtT is straightforward."

#: ../../source/intranet/windows/domain/attack.rst:54
msgid "Kerberoasting Attacks"
msgstr "Kerberoasting Attacks"

#: ../../source/intranet/windows/domain/attack.rst:55
msgid ""
"Kerberoasting攻击由Tim Medin在2014 DerbyCon conference上 `公开 "
"<https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=PUyhlN-E5MU>`_ "
"。指域内的任何一台主机，都可以通过查询SPN，Kerberoasting即是向域内的所有服务请求TGS，然后进行暴力破解。"
msgstr "Kerberoasting was `publicly presented <https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=PUyhlN-E5MU>`_ by Tim Medin at the 2014 DerbyCon conference. Any host in a domain can query SPNs; Kerberoasting requests TGS tickets for all services in the domain and then brute-forces them."

#: ../../source/intranet/windows/domain/attack.rst:58
msgid "Roasting AS-REP"
msgstr "Roasting AS-REP"

#: ../../source/intranet/windows/domain/attack.rst:59
msgid ""
"该攻击枚举域中不需要Kerberos预身份认证的帐户，向这些账户请求一条加密信息，并离线尝试获取到的账户哈希。该方式需要账户明确设置了 "
"``DONT_REQ_PREAUTH`` 。"
msgstr "This attack enumerates accounts in the domain that do not require Kerberos pre-authentication, requests encrypted data for those accounts, and attempts to recover the obtained account hashes offline. This method requires the account to have ``DONT_REQ_PREAUTH`` explicitly set."

#: ../../source/intranet/windows/domain/attack.rst:62
msgid "Kerberos Delegation Attacks"
msgstr "Kerberos Delegation Attacks"

#: ../../source/intranet/windows/domain/attack.rst:63
msgid ""
"在一个域中，A使用Kerberos身份验证访问服务B，B再使用A的身份去访问C，这个过程就可以理解为委派。委派主要分为非约束委派（Unconstrained"
" delegation）和约束委派（Constrained "
"delegation）两种，非约束委派可以访问域内任意其它服务，约束委派对认证做了限制不可以访问其他的服务。"
msgstr "In a domain, if A uses Kerberos authentication to access service B and B then uses A's identity to access C, this process can be understood as delegation. Delegation is mainly divided into Unconstrained delegation and Constrained delegation. Unconstrained delegation can access any other service in the domain, while constrained delegation restricts authentication and cannot access other services."

#: ../../source/intranet/windows/domain/attack.rst:65
msgid ""
"Kerberos "
"Delegation（Kerberos委派）攻击分为非约束委派攻击和约束委派攻击。原理都是基于域内已经配置了委派的账户来获取其它账户的权限。"
msgstr "Kerberos Delegation attacks are divided into unconstrained delegation attacks and constrained delegation attacks. Both are based on using accounts in the domain that have already been configured for delegation to obtain other accounts' privileges."

